No student should sit in a classroom with a teacher who glorifies violence. After a MSU Mankato professor’s reprehensible remarks on Charlie Kirk, and his history of inflammatory language, I urge the university to act. Students deserve an education rooted in respect, integrity, and safety.
Calling out these dangers isn’t politics, like some claimed; It’s protecting our communities. I will continue to stand with my colleagues pushing to improve forest management and wildfire prevention.

I had a productive discussion this week with the Minnesota State Cattlemen’s Association on priorities like disease prevention and CRP flexibility. With 2.4 million head of cattle in our state, I’ll continue working to ensure #MN01 cattle producers have the tools to grow and compete globally.

Great to speak with local leaders at the Minnesota Transportation Alliance Breakfast this morning to discuss the upcoming Surface Transportation Reauthorization. I look forward to continuing our federal, state, and local partnerships to ensure Minnesota’s communities have reliable infrastructure.

Hard work. Long hours. Miles away from home. From hauling crops out of southern Minnesota fields to delivering goods nationwide, truckers keep our communities strong. Grateful this week, and every week, for the trucking industry and the families who keep our economy moving. #ThankATrucker

Here in southern Minnesota and from coast to coast, small businesses depend on support that works. The Working Families Tax Cuts deliver that. Thank you, @RepRWilliams, for fighting for Main Street and working families.

Always good to meet with my friends @MinnesotaPork! I recently introduced the American Protein Processing Modernization Act to ensure producers in #MN01 can count on safe, efficient processing. I’ll always stand with the farm families who put food on our tables. https://t.co/mg1kDEoKLO

Yesterday, I met with southern Minnesota biofuel producers with @GrowthEnergy to discuss the need for immediate, nationwide access to year-round E15 and the implementation of the 45Z clean fuel production tax credit.  I was also honored to receive the 2025 Fueling Growth Award! https://t.co/O9FvxyUdx8

May we always remember the men and women who lost their lives on this terrible day 24 years ago and the first responders who were on the front line serving their neighbors in the wake of this vicious attack on American soil. In their honor, we pledge to #NeverForget. https://t.co/b6FkodB0vB

Charlie Kirk was such a bright mind and light to this world. His faith, knowledge, and voice inspired so many. Let’s not allow evil to win by letting his work die with him, but instead pray that those who have heard him will use their faith and reason to be beacons of hope, common sense, and courage…out of darkness will come light.

The #FY26NDAA puts our military in a position to restore Peace Through Strength. Glad to see this legislation pass today & proud of our work on @HASCRepublicans to fulfill our commitment to our country’s servicemembers, their families, & all Americans. https://t.co/ATK81cLHIB
Shocked by the horrific attack on Charlie Kirk. Political violence of this nature has no place in our country. I am praying for Charlie and his family. https://t.co/7VzfegKCaI

Grateful to be presented with the Defender of Limited Government Award. In Congress, I’ll keep fighting for responsible policies that rein in government overreach on behalf of southern MN families, farmers, & small businesses. Thank you @leganalysis! https://t.co/jwdD2F4nYz

Honored to recognize the grand opening of MSU Mankato’s Maverick Innovation Gateway. This new center will equip students with real-world skills, foster entrepreneurship, and keep southern Minnesota at the forefront of innovation. https://t.co/Ajmz0zLvK2

75 indictments and counting. These are YOUR taxpayer dollars that were meant to feed hungry kids and instead went to buy Kenyan real estate. The lack of oversight of state-administered dollars should outrage each and every one of us.

Today, I spoke on the House Floor to honor the life of Jake Larson, known to many as “Papa Jake”, a true American hero and beloved storyteller. From storming the beaches of Normandy to inspiring millions online with his humor and humility, Jake’s courage and kindness left a mark on us all. His legacy will live on through the many lives he touched.

Proud to join @chelliepingree and @SenTinaSmith in introducing the bipartisan ASPIRE Act, legislation which invests in the next generation of farmers by strengthening resources for hands-on training programs, apprenticeships, and partnerships with local ag businesses. https://t.co/jMImCVht0P

It was an honor to welcome @USDA Under Secretary for Trade Luke Lindberg to southern Minnesota this week. I appreciated our discussion on opening new markets, reducing reliance on China, and ensuring Minnesota’s farmers have the certainty and access they need to compete. I’m grateful for his willingness to hear directly from #MN01 farmers, and I look forward to working alongside him to deliver better deals for U.S. producers.

Southern Minnesota is fortunate to have one of the nation’s largest manufacturers of cement mixers and garbage trucks right here in Dodge Center. I joined @CTMMixers owner, Grant McNeilus, for a tour of their growing operation, now with over 300 employees. We discussed their commitment to performance, safety, and service. Thanks to Grant and Garwin for the hospitality!

Today our entire Minnesota delegation joined together for a moment of silence on the House Floor to honor the victims and stand with a grieving community after last week’s tragedy at Annunciation Catholic School. May God continue to bring comfort and healing to the students, families, teachers, and all who have been affected by this senseless violence.

Proud to welcome EPA Administrator @epaleezeldin to #MN01 for a tour and roundtable at @CF_Farms in Brown County. In the Trump Administration, farm country has a seat at the table and federal leaders listen directly to the needs of our producers. Our discussion focused on the challenges facing livestock producers and the importance of policies that allow agriculture to thrive.

Grateful to my friend, Dr. Jeff Boyd, and the outstanding team at RCTC for sharing updates on the exciting developments happening across campus. Their outstanding vocational programs and their continued commitment to meeting the needs of our local economy makes RCTC an invaluable part of our #MN01 community.
Today we recognize the commitment of the hard workers who build and strengthen our communities. Wishing all in #MN01 a safe and happy Labor Day. https://t.co/YJJiNdkrwJ

Applauding Fort Hood’s new hearing protection upgrades which are key to safeguarding our troops' health and boosting readiness. Proud to support efforts like this on @HASC. Thanks to Starkey SoundGear for helping make it happen! 
https://t.co/f514ap41Io

Excellent to meet with Dr. Ritu Raju, the new President of @SCCollege! We’re excited to welcome her to Minnesota, and I know South Central College will continue to serve its students and our #MN01 community well under her leadership. https://t.co/WYjZHtrV72

Rasmussen University has 6 campuses across the state, offering 50+ programs in 8 areas of study. I appreciated the tour and discussion at the Mankato campus where I got to see their top-of-the-line Nursing Simulation Lab, which prepares so many of our nurses in southern Minnesota. Thanks to @Rasmussen for having me and State Rep. Erica Schwartz for joining, as well.

Founded in the Midwest, Jack Links has grown to a global company and remains a snacking staple in #MN01. As they celebrate 40 years in the meat snack industry, it was an honor to tour the Jack Links Mankato plant, an operation that produces 6.4 million pounds of packaged product per year. Thanks to the whole team at @JackLinks for the warm welcome!

Thank you to the numerous law enforcement personnel responding to this heartbreaking scene this morning. Keeping the students, teachers, and all of Minnesota in my prayers in the wake of today's horrific violence. https://t.co/W2NnpylqCn

Today I introduced the American Protein Processing Modernization Act to provide long-term certainty for America’s food supply chain. This legislation ensures safe, science-based processing, protects farmers’ livelihoods, and strengthens our nation’s food security.
https://t.co/vtfHTSV0pd

Met with Crossroads Trailers in Albert Lea last week to hear about their operation and have an important discussion on the economic outlook, the regulatory landscape, and how @HouseSmallBiz Committee can best serve small businesses. Thankful to have SBA Deputy Administrator Bill Briggs join the conversation.

Visited @InkitHQ's new space to hear about the work they do to support the Department of Defense and hear about their priorities for upcoming NDAA and Appropriations legislation. As a member of @HASCRepublicans, it’s exciting to see a Minnesota company leading in digital transformation.”

The Broadway in Albert Lea is a great example of local groups coming together to revitalize a historic space. Cento has already been open for nearly a year, and the space is almost fully renovated. With several businesses currently operating and more on the way, this landmark continues to strengthen downtown and preserve city history. Glad I could stop by last week to see the great work being done!

Last week, I had the opportunity to hear from the folks at Recovery in Motion and see firsthand the dedication they show to helping our neighbors in need of recovery. While touring their treatment center in Fairmont, we talked about ways we can ensure policies at the federal level best serve the organizations that administer substance use disorder treatment services, as well as our community members who rely on them.

Great to tour of the brand-new Design Ready Controls Albert Lea facility with @SBADeputy_Bill! Proud to see American manufacturing thriving here in #MN01 & talk about how pro-growth policies are building stronger communities.

This week, I joined Southeast MN farmers and EPA Region 5 Administrator Anne Vogel to discuss reversing the Biden Admin's regulatory overreach in response to politically motivated, anti-agriculture activists. Farmers are the best environmentalists in the world and work every day to preserve their land, water, and air for future generations.
Thank you to the Smith family for hosting!

I joined the Austin Chamber of Commerce with @SBADeputy_Bill for a roundtable discussion on how federal policy can best support Austin’s small business community and local families. These conversations are vital to ensuring southern Minnesota’s priorities are represented in Washington.

One of the most important parts of serving in Congress is hearing directly from city and county leaders about the issues affecting our #MN01 communities. I had a productive meeting at the Waseca Art Center, where I met with area business owners and city leaders to give an update on what’s going on in Washington and ways we can strengthen the partnership between city, state, and federal government.

Nice to be back in Jackson to join city staff for an update on the ways they are working to revitalize economic development downtown. We also discussed the FEMA response to last year’s catastrophic flooding, as well as the ongoing challenges the city is facing with rural healthcare and an increased demand for housing. Thanks for the visit!

USDA announced it will end taxpayer handouts for solar power plants on prime farmland. This is a big win for farmers, food security, and the next generation who shouldn't have to compete against the federal government for the highest quality soil in the world. Proud to stand with Secretary Rollins in putting America’s farmers first.

I recently had the honor of meeting with Rabbis David and Shloime Greene of Chabad of Southern Minnesota and Mayo Clinic Area. The two of them presented me with the Book of Jewish Knowledge, which holds the rich history, timeless traditions, and the proud heritage of the Jewish people. I am grateful we were able to discuss the importance of youth education, combatting antisemitism, and the Jewish community in southern Minnesota.

Thank you to the MN Ag Leadership Conference for inviting me to speak today! Representing southern Minnesota’s hardworking farmers in Congress is the honor of a lifetime. We’ve already delivered 80% of the Farm Bill through the One Big Beautiful Bill, and I’ll keep fighting every day for farm country.

It was a great day at the Steele County Fair, which I’m always proud to say has been the largest county fair in Minnesota for over 80 years. With more than 500 booths, 100 food stands, carnival games, and rides, it was a fun day to connect with many fairgoers, and wonderful to see Fair Director and friend, Scott Kozelka, along with my friend, former Mayor, Tom Kuntz and his wife, Shelby.

I was honored to tour @flyrst with Executive Director John Reed and city officials earlier this week and see firsthand the progress being made on their runway expansion. Excited for the many ways this project will support future growth and improve passenger experience at RST. https://t.co/PeSTSUtByr

Thanks to @greatermankato for hosting me for this week’s business roundtable. We talked about recent federal legislation, my priorities in Congress, and how the One Big Beautiful Bill strengthens our small businesses and #MN01 communities. I’m grateful to the folks who took the time to share their perspectives and be part of this important conversation.

For my team and I, crime in D.C. is personal. I support @POTUS taking the actions necessary to keep our capital safe for those who live there and the thousands of southern Minnesotans who visit every year. https://t.co/KQrCjJ3N6n

Last night at the Lafayette City Council meeting, we celebrated a truly special milestone: Lafayette’s 125th Anniversary. It was an honor to present a flag flown over the U.S. Capitol and a Certificate of Congressional Recognition to mark 125 years of community, heritage, and tradition in southern Minnesota.
Congratulations, Lafayette!

Always proud to serve #MN01, the #2 pork-producing district in the country! In Congress, I'm committed to making sure our livestock producers can do what they do best: putting safe and nutritious protein on our tables. Thanks, @MinnesotaPork for a great visit at Farmfest!” https://t.co/J0a4SfwtOg

A day at Farmfest wouldn't be complete without the smell of beef cooking at the Minnesota State Cattlemen's Association tent. It was great to catch up with their folks last week to hear about their legislative priorities and ways we're working in Congress to strengthen trade programs for our U.S. beef producers.

I was proud to meet with the @MNSoyGrowers at Farmfest this week. Their advocacy for vital policies like protecting crop inputs, supporting biodiesel, and easing tax burdens is more important than ever. I will continue fighting to ensure farm policy delivers a strong safety net, boosts export opportunities, and gives farmers the certainty they need to keep feeding and fueling the world.”

Families across #MN01 rely on nonprofit community health centers for affordable medical and dental services. I recently met with Open Door Health Center to talk with their team about the shortage of physicians and dentists impacting their services and ways we can work to keep talented healthcare professionals in rural areas, especially for the many patients who depend on federally qualified health centers (FQHCs) for their care. Thanks for having me!

It was good to meet with Compeer Financial at Minnesota Farmfest this week. Ag lenders, like Compeer, are a valuable part of our rural farming communities, providing the access to credit that help farmers succeed here in #MN01, and across our state and country. https://t.co/g99lTCcXNo

The One Big Beautiful Bill strengthens Medicaid for those who need it. Democrats would rather fearmonger than get on board.

With rising input costs and low profitability rates in recent years, I know firsthand the challenges our country’s farmers are facing, and the importance of strong farm policy that meets the needs of those who feed and fuel the world.

I've always been proud to be a voice for our #MN01 corn growers, which is why my @HouseAgGOP colleagues and I have worked hard to include provisions in The One Big Beautiful Bill that deliver a strong safety net, increased funding for export promotion, and – most of all – provides certainty to our @mncorn farming families.

I had the honor of providing a House Ag Committee update at the Sweetener Symposium as we celebrated 40 years of the @SugarAlliance bringing together folks from across the sugar industry. I’m committed to defending American food security and ensuring our farmers can feed the world for generations to come.

By opening 529 savings plans to training & credentialing programs, we are equipping students to meet the demands of today's workforce.

Proud to have championed this issue in Congress, & glad to see this win for #MN01 students & families.

It was great to visit with members of the Faribault Chamber of Commerce last week. As a member of the @HouseSmallBiz Committee, I appreciated hearing from local business owners about the challenges they are facing and how we can support economic growth in our communities. Thanks for having me, I appreciate hearing from local business owners!

What a fantastic day at @MNFarmfest, welcoming @USDA Deputy Secretary Stephen Vaden to our great state. I’ve been proud to work alongside @RepFischbach and @RepPeteStauber in delivering historic wins for our farmers and ag producers, like:
✅making the Death Tax exemption permanent
✅strengthening the farm safety net
✅increasing investment in combatting and preventing foreign animal diseases
✅doubling funding for trade promotion programs

But there’s still more work to be done to address the challenges our #MN01 farmers are facing. Looking forward to joining my @HouseAgGOP colleagues to get the remaining pieces of the farm bill across the finish line.

I had the honor of visiting with @Semcac in Faribault this week. Their dedication to providing essential services and empowering folks makes a lasting impact across our entire district. It was great to sit down with them and talk about the work that they are doing to strengthen communities across #MN01.

https://t.co/L6hfPxU9Qn

Canadian politicians and even some in our own media might want us to stay quiet, but we deserve answers on what their plan is to finally address this persistent, cross-border crisis moving forward

This week, I hosted a veteran’s roundtable to hear directly from those who served how Congress can help address the challenges veterans are facing. Our veterans deserve local access to mental health care, peer support, and transition resources, without having to travel for hours for help. It’s time we brought these vital services closer to home, which is why I’m leading legislation to bring a VA Vet Center to the heart of south-central Minnesota. 🇺🇸#SupportOurVeterans #MankatoVetCenter

As a fourth-generation farmer, I’m honored to serve as Vice Chair of Emerging Innovations for the Modern Ag Caucus. American farmers are the most efficient in the world, and I look forward to working with my colleagues to promote the cutting-edge technology that helps feed and fuel the world.

Thank you to those who put in the early mornings and late nights to provide us with the milk, cheese, butter, and ice cream we love.

As a member of both @HASCRepublicans and @HouseSmallBiz, I was glad to take part in this week’s hearing to discuss the important role critical minerals play in our national security. As our reliance on minerals like copper, nickel, and cobalt increases, so does our reliance on China and other foreign adversaries for our critical mineral needs.

I know the people of #MN01 would rather rely on our neighbors here at home to extract and refine these minerals for our domestic supply chain, which is why I asked some of the top leaders in the mining industry what steps we can take to bring more critical mineral development to our backyard.

I always love showing Minnesotans around the Capitol, especially our young leaders. Yesterday, @RepFischbach and I had the chance to talk with awesome @MN4H students who traveled to D.C. for the Citizenship Washington Focus program, which helps teens grow their leadership and communication skills as they learn about our nation’s history, democracy, and Constitution.

Today @TheJusticeDept sued @GovTimWalz and the State of Minnesota to prevent illegal immigrants from receiving in-state tuition at universities in our state.
 
@AgPamBondi is right when she says “No state can be allowed to treat Americans like second-class citizens in their own country.” Thankful for DOJ’s continued efforts to restore commonsense polices to our state!

Whether we agree or disagree on policy issues, politically targeted violence must never be tolerated.
